    <content type="html">&lt;p&gt;It&amp;rsquo;s was the end of the quarter and we needed to build out some sweet reports to show off awesome widget sales performance. There&amp;rsquo;s going to be all kinds of charts and graphs going on. The good news is we get them all for &lt;a href="http://www.chartjs.org/"&gt;free!&lt;/a&gt; I only need to provide a suite of API endpoints for Chart.js to load the data from. Having a wide variety of charts and graphs is only part of the equation. If you&amp;rsquo;re going gor &lt;em&gt;maximum&lt;/em&gt; impact you&amp;rsquo;re going to need some radical colors to fill up the page. And thats why I created &lt;code&gt;ColorSampler&lt;/code&gt;, behold:&lt;/p&gt;
